parameters:
The checkpoint over there is heavily guarded... Since its
establishment, no one has ever broken through. If you want
to pass, you'll need to obtain a pass.
I can't handle this without drinking. *hic*...
I love it best when I'm fishing leisurely.

What? Are you going back to Edo for a bit? We'll be waiting
here, so come back quickly once you're done.

What? Are you going back to Edo for a bit? We'll be waiting
here, so come back quickly once you're done.

If you wish to pass through this checkpoint, you need a
[Pass Permit]. If you don't have one, you should turn back.
Indeed. You have the pass. You may proceed--

...We simply fulfill our duties. There's no point in
pondering over it, as it leads nowhere.

If you have a pass, you can go through the checkpoint as
many times as you want. It's also important to return to Edo
if you're missing any tools.

I've heard that the garrison in Sagami has also gone up in
flames, and I'm very worried. The other day, a colleague of
mine went to guard the garrison as an assistant... I hope
he's safe and sound without any incidents...

If the checkpoint is breached, it's a matter for seppuku.
That's why I'm devoted to swordsmanship even on holidays.

I heard that the castle was set ablaze by demons, but could
it be just a rumor? It's so hard to believe...

No good, no good. Even using a bribe won't do. Don't think
you can buy the guardians of the law with money!

Please... please let me through! My pass was stolen by
thieves...! If you let me through the checkpoint, I'll give
you all the money I have...!

Ever since the bridge to Edo was completed, the number of
people staying at the inn here has decreased... I've decided
to close up shop. Perhaps this is just the way of the
times...

South of this checkpoint is the province of Shimousa.
Travelers say there's an eerie forest, but I wonder if it
really exists...

I just delivered a letter to the client and now I'm taking a
break. Man, I really ran a lot this time too. I love
running, so being a courier is the perfect job for me.

...Honestly, dropping the pass permit like that... I can't
entrust Karin with Key Items...
It's okay, Karin-chan. We'll be waiting here for you.
Sorry to keep you both waiting! My apologies for being late!
Oh? Did you find the pass?

That's great, Karin-chan. Now, let's head to the Forest of
Spirits--
Gatekeeper-san, we can pass through with this, right?

Hmm. This is a genuine pass--glad you found it. Go ahead and
pass through.

Yay! Now we can go through the checkpoint with our heads
held high♪

Now, our destination is the Forest of Spirits to the south
from here.

The Forest of Spirits is a place I'm also familiar with. I
can guide us there, so let's get going--
\c[17]--Yugiri and Momiji have joined the party!\c[0]

Hey! Those without a pass cannot go through! If you try to
force your way past, I'll throw you in jail!
(Ugh... To think I dropped my pass... How shameful...)
\c[17]--Yugiri, Momiji, and Masaki have joined your party!\c[0]
\c[17]--Yugiri and Momiji have joined your party!\c[0]

First, I need to go see Momiji-san. Let's try going to the
pleasure district at night--
I'm sorry for making you wait!
You're late, Karin? It's already noon, you know?
We're now entering Shimousa. Let's cross the checkpoint.

Are you three girls traveling together? If you wish to pass
through the gate, show me your travel permits.

...What seems to be the matter? Don't tell me you don't have
your travel permit?
What's wrong, Karin? Don't tell me...

Did you lose the travel permit you got from the magistrate's
office yesterday?

Ugh, no way...! I definitely received the permit, but I
rushed home and might have dropped it on the way back... I
can't find it...

You really are hopeless. Travel permits aren't something you
can just casually reissue. What are you planning to do,
Karin?

If you dropped it, then let's look for it together, Karin-
chan.

No, it's my fault, so I'll go look for it right away. Sorry
to both of you--

--Karin decided to retrace her steps in search of the lost
travel permit.
